aracter of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Nunwicke was born in 1342, her father, Thomas Nunwyke, was 43 and her mother, Johanna Hertforth, was 50. She married Adam Norton in 1351, in Ripon, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died about 1402, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1342–Abt 1402":"1342–umbes 1402","1342–1402":"1342–1402","1334–1400":"1334–1400","1352–1411":"1352–1411","1360–1420":"1360–1420","1300–1370":"1300–1370","1292–Female":"1292–Surnud","about 1360":"umbes 1360","1352":"1352","1351":"1351","Abt 1402":"umbes 1402","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1292":"1292","1402":"1402","1400":"1400","1411":"1411","1334":"1334","1300":"1300","1420":"1420","1342":"1342","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Hartismere, Suffolk, England":"Hartismere, Suffolk, England","Urswick, England":"Great Urswick, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ripon, Yorkshire, England":"Ripon, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1342–Abt 1402":"1342–noin 1402","1342–1402":"1342–1402","1334–1400":"1334–1400","1352–1411":"1352–1411","1360–1420":"1360–1420","1300–1370":"1300–1370","1292–Female":"1292–Kuollut","about 1360":"noin 1360","1352":"1352","1351":"1351","Abt 1402":"noin 1402","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1292":"1292","1402":"1402","1400":"1400","1411":"1411","1334":"1334","1300":"1300","1420":"1420","1342":"1342","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Hartismere, Suffolk, England":"Hartismere, Suffolk, England","Urswick, England":"Great Urswick, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ripon, Yorkshire, England":"Ripon, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"134